The paper focuses on using Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) to predict the ultimate bearing capacity of shallow foundation in situations when the experimental data which may be used to train networks is scarce. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves comparing the performance of different DNN architectures, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves testing the accuracy of the DNNs in predicting the ultimate bearing capacity of shallow foundations, which suggests that it may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
